1. Introduction:
The AI-Powered Customer Support Ticketing System is a Salesforce-based application designed to improve customer support operations by automating ticket management and providing intelligent assistance to support agents. The system centralizes customer interactions and support requests using Salesforce standard and custom objects.
By using automation features such as Record-Triggered Flows, the application automatically classifies support cases, assigns priorities, calculates SLA due dates, and sends notifications. This reduces manual effort and improves response time and customer satisfaction.
The system also provides AI-assisted responses and feedback mechanisms to support agents, helping organizations improve support quality and operational efficiency.
________________________________________
2. Problem Statement
Many organizations still manage customer support requests manually, which can lead to delayed responses, inconsistent prioritization, missed SLA deadlines, and poor customer experience. Support teams often struggle to track large volumes of cases and ensure timely resolution.
There is a need for an automated and intelligent support system that can classify cases, prioritize them based on severity, track SLA compliance, and assist support agents in resolving issues quickly and efficiently.
________________________________________
3. Objectives
The main objectives of the project are:
•	To automate customer support ticket management. 
•	To classify support cases automatically based on issue type. 
•	To assign priorities to cases according to business rules. 
•	To calculate and monitor SLA due dates. 
•	To provide AI-assisted suggested replies for support agents. 
•	To improve customer satisfaction by reducing response times. 
•	To provide reports and dashboards for performance monitoring.
________________________________________
4. Functional Scope:
The functional scope of the AI-Powered Customer Support Ticketing System defines the major features and capabilities provided by the application. The system is designed to improve customer support efficiency by automating repetitive tasks and assisting support agents in handling customer issues.
The application allows users to create and manage customer support cases using the Salesforce Case object. Cases are automatically classified based on issue type and assigned an appropriate priority level using automation rules and flows.
The system calculates SLA due dates based on predefined business policies to ensure timely issue resolution. Support agents can update case status, review AI-generated suggested replies, and communicate effectively with customers.
An AI feedback mechanism is also included, allowing support agents to provide feedback on the quality and usefulness of AI-generated suggestions. This helps in continuously improving system performance and recommendation quality.
The application also includes reports and dashboards for monitoring case volume, SLA compliance, and agent performance.
________________________________________
5. Stakeholder Mapping
Stakeholder mapping identifies all individuals and groups involved in the development, management, and usage of the AI-Powered Customer Support Ticketing System.
Customers
Customers are the end users who create support requests and expect timely issue resolution and communication.
Support Agents
Support agents are responsible for reviewing, updating, and resolving customer cases. They use AI-generated suggestions to improve response quality and efficiency.
Support Managers
Support managers monitor support team performance, review SLA compliance, and analyze reports and dashboards to improve operational efficiency.
System Administrators
System administrators configure Salesforce objects, flows, security settings, and automation components while ensuring system stability and security.
Business Stakeholders
Business stakeholders define business requirements and ensure that the implemented solution aligns with organizational objectives and customer service goals.
________________________________________
6. Data Model and System Architecture
The AI-Powered Customer Support Ticketing System uses a combination of Salesforce standard objects and custom objects to manage customer information, support requests, SLA policies, and AI feedback efficiently.
The data model is designed to maintain proper relationships between customers, support cases, and support teams while enabling automation and reporting capabilities.
________________________________________
Standard Objects Used
Account
The Account object stores customer organization information such as company name, industry, phone number, and account type. It acts as the parent object for contacts and support cases.
Fields Used:
•	Account Name 
•	Phone 
•	Industry 
•	Type 
Contact
The Contact object stores customer details including name, email address, and phone number. Contacts are associated with Accounts and Cases.
Fields Used:
•	First Name 
•	Last Name 
•	Email 
•	Phone 
Case
The Case object is the core object used to manage customer support tickets and issue resolution activities.
Fields Used:
•	Case Number 
•	Subject 
•	Description 
•	Status 
•	Priority 
•	Issue Type 
•	SLA Due Date 
•	AI Suggested Reply 
•	Resolution Time 
________________________________________
Custom Objects Used
Support_Category__c
This object stores various support categories and their default priorities.
Fields:
•	Category Name 
•	Description 
•	Default Priority 
•	Active 
SLA_Policy__c
This object stores SLA rules for different priority levels and issue categories.
Fields:
•	Policy Name 
•	Priority Level 
•	Resolution Time (Hours) 
•	Escalation Required 
AI_Feedback__c
This object stores agent feedback regarding AI-generated suggestions.
Fields:
•	AI Feedback Number 
•	AI Suggestion Type 
•	Feedback Status 
•	Agent Comments 
________________________________________

7. Automation Using Salesforce Flows
The AI-Powered Customer Support Ticketing System uses Salesforce Record-Triggered Flows to automate various support processes and reduce manual effort.
Automatic Case Classification
When a new case is created, the system automatically analyzes the issue type and assigns an appropriate support category.
Priority Assignment
The system assigns High, Medium, or Low priority to cases based on predefined business rules and issue severity.
SLA Due Date Calculation
Based on the case priority and SLA policy, the system automatically calculates the SLA due date and stores it in the Case record.
Email Notifications
When a case status changes to Closed, an automated email notification is sent to the customer informing them that their issue has been resolved.
AI Suggested Responses
The system generates suggested replies for support agents using Agentforce Prompt Templates. Agents can review and modify these suggestions before sending them to customers.
________________________________________
8. Security Model:
The project uses Salesforce Profiles and Permission Sets to implement role-based access control.
Support Agent
•	Can create and update cases. 
•	Can provide AI feedback. 
•	Has read-only access to customer information. 
Support Manager
•	Can monitor cases and agent performance. 
•	Has access to reports and dashboards. 
•	Can update priorities and ownership details. 
System Administrator
•	Has complete access to all objects, flows, reports, and security settings. 
•	Responsible for maintaining and configuring the system. 
Permission Sets are used to provide additional access to AI features and reporting functionality whenever required.
________________________________________
9. Reports and Monitoring
The project includes reports and dashboards that help managers monitor support activities and business performance.
Open Cases by Priority
This report displays all open support cases grouped by priority level, helping managers identify critical issues quickly.
Agent Performance Report
This report measures support agent productivity by tracking resolution times and workloads.
SLA Monitoring
Managers can identify overdue cases and SLA violations to ensure customer commitments are met.
________________________________________
10. Conclusion
The AI-Powered Customer Support Ticketing System successfully demonstrates the use of Salesforce automation and AI capabilities in customer support operations.
By combining standard objects, custom objects, flows, validation rules, profiles, permission sets, and Agentforce features, the system reduces manual effort and improves support efficiency.
The implementation provides centralized case management, SLA tracking, intelligent agent assistance, and performance monitoring, making it a scalable and maintainable solution for modern customer support environments.



